item.content:encoded: Hi there, I use Acer Predator Helios 300. It is a gaming laptop for those who don't know. Since I am currently in first year of my college so I don't need much intense work and also I do light gaming in my free time, so it does it's job. I have been using it for the past two months and had no issues. Love it. Rig is powered by Intel processor i7 8th Gen, 8 GB RAM, 1 TB HDD, 128 GB SSD and Nvidia 1050 Ti 4 GB graphics card. This is my first personal laptop. My elder brother bought it for me, so I consider it as a gift from his side because of which I care a lot about this laptop and won't let it happen anything. item.title: Going back.
item.dc:creator: akapksenpai
item.content:encoded:
Semester End. I haven't been home in Lucknow since I started University, this is first I'm going home. I don't know how should I feel, they are my family and also when started first there was lot of hard time and I was always thinking to go back but now when time came I'm don't know if I want to. Even though I don't think I have a choice. I wonder do everyone is feeling like going back. I seen people feeling nothing from the first day and enjoying their life but what if they were just portraing to look happy so that no one know that they were hurting inside and missing home. We may never know.
I came to Bangalore by bus. I meet one person from my Hostel I don't remember his name but he asked to join me cause he didn't had cash to get a cab so I agreed even though I would have agreed. I came to my brother's house. I would be staying with him for a day and then tomorrow I have flight at 11:15 AM. Feeling good at my brother's and don't want to go. He ordered food and ice-cream from Swiggy, We played PUBG the whole day, and even had worderful chats, it was fun but as I said time is inevitable.
Here I am in Bangalore Airport, people here seems more involved in there own lives. I took boarding pass, went through security gate and sat in from the gate from where the boarding will start. Environment was quite busy, hardly anyone care what the person next to them are doing. Here I am seeing a lot of foreign people and they are boarding domestic flights. I see this girl in a cafe, she was cute but I know I have no courage to ask her even her name so I left. I am standing across the wall. People are sitting and the Indigo boarding person is doing his job but it looks like he is very slow. Boarding time came people started making line and the cute girl was in the front. Indigo person was behind his desk and was not starting. I wonder what his life would be like, working whole time at the airport, doing same thing every single time.
We are in the plane, I am starting to make my way through people, going toward my seat, 27A. I sat, and you wouldn't believe me but the cute girl was having her seat next to me, what a luck but no luck. I thought at some point she would talk by saying "What's Up?" But it was just a dream. Plane went up and came down, no progress. I think nothing would happen for me, I will live alone forever. Came out, booked a cab and started walking toward it and all the private taxi started there marketing, made my way through them. Reached my home, standing outside the door and thinking should I or should I not. I went inside. Everything was back to normal like I never went away. No outcast feeling, no nothing. Still this is my first day don't know how the whole month will go like.
